You can schedule a dataflow to run after an event, such as when a sync job completes. Or you can schedule it to run hourly, weekly, monthly, or on specific days of the week or dates.

To schedule a dataflow:
Click Data Manager in the left pane.
Click the Dataflows & Recipes tab.
Select Schedule from the menu.
Choose Event-based under Schedule Mode, and select the event that triggers the dataflow.
Or choose Time-based under Schedule Mode, and select the time to run the dataflow.

You can also use Stop queuing at a specific time to stop the schedule from adding more dataflow runs to the queue after a certain time.

Click Save.

Schedules for data sync, dataflow, and recipes are removed 30 days after the last save in Sandbox and Developer edition orgs, and 10 days after the last save in Trial orgs. Users subscribed to notifications receive an email when a schedule is removed.
title: Automatically Schedule Salesforce Dataflows
